# PR Lifecycle

## Creating

1. Commit with a descriptive conventional-commit message.
2. Push: `git push -u origin HEAD`
3. Open PR: `gh pr create` with summary and test plan.

## CI Monitoring

1. Poll: `gh pr checks <PR-NUMBER>` until all checks complete.
2. On failure, read logs: `gh run view <RUN-ID> --job <JOB-ID> --log-failed`
3. Fix in the worktree, commit, push, re-monitor.
4. If failure is unrelated (e.g. billing/infra), note it and proceed.

## Copilot Review

1. Request: `gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{number}/requested_reviewers --method POST -f 'reviewers[]=copilot'`
2. Poll for review: `gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{number}/reviews --jq 'if length > 0 then .[-1] | {author: .user.login, state: .state} else {author: null, state: "NO_REVIEWS"} end'`
3. Fetch inline comments: `gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{number}/comments`
4. Fix comments, push, re-request review.

## Merging

- Squash merge: `gh pr merge <number> --squash --body "..."`
- After merge: `git checkout main && git pull`

## Impactful PR Gate (required before merge)

Run a **real ARO e2e deployment probe** for impactful PRs before merge.

Treat a PR as impactful when it changes any of:
- frontend gameplay UX/layout or user flows
- backend API/chat/scoring/session behavior
- deployment scripts, Helm values, or route wiring
- infrastructure or environment plumbing used by runtime paths

Required gate for impactful PRs:
1. Ensure required vars are available in `backend/.env.local`.
2. Run `make e2e-azure-route` from the task worktree.
3. Confirm probe readiness (`Probe status: 200`) and capture namespace + URL in the PR comment or final handoff.
4. Keep the temporary namespace until reviewer signoff, then clean up with `make e2e-azure-route-down` (or `NS=<namespace> make e2e-azure-route-down`).

## Checklist (complete ALL before finishing)

- [ ] `make validate` passes
- [ ] `make test` passes
- [ ] `make test-integration` passes
- [ ] For impactful PRs: `make e2e-azure-route` passes with probe status 200
- [ ] PR created with summary
- [ ] CI checks green (or confirmed unrelated failure)
- [ ] PR URL and status reported to user
